# GGX Business+ — build-time env (Vite; must be prefixed VITE_).
# Copy to .env.local for local development. Both are OPTIONAL: sensible deployed
# defaults are baked in, so the hosted app works without setting anything.

# ─── HeyQ integration ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# HeyQ ships as two pieces on two origins. Business+ needs both:

# The HeyQ API origin (standalone Railway service). Business+ reads tickets and
# posts requester replies/reopens here. No trailing slash, no /api suffix —
# requests resolve to ${VITE_HEYQ_API_URL}/api/...
# Default: https://heyq-api-production.up.railway.app
# Local against a local HeyQ API: http://localhost:4310
VITE_HEYQ_API_URL=

# The HeyQ FRONTEND origin — used only to OPEN HeyQ pages (the contact form for
# ticket submission, the requester portal). NOT the API.
# Default: https://heyq.vercel.app
# Local against a local HeyQ frontend: http://localhost:18020
VITE_HEYQ_URL=
